    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Add critical failure log for schedule_ue_spec when no data to transmit\n\n### Summary\nThe `schedule_ue_spec` function in `eNB_scheduler_dlsch.c` was missing critical logging when no data was available to transmit for a scheduled UE. This made debugging downstream issues difficult as there was no indication why a UE was being skipped.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_dlsch.c`: Added warning log statement when `ta_len + sdu_length_total + header_length_total <= 0` to indicate no data to transmit for UE\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running OAI eNB with connected UEs, occasionally UEs would be scheduled but no data would be transmitted. Without this log statement, there was no visibility into whether:\n1. RLC had no data available for the UE\n2. Timing advance calculations resulted in no data to send\n3. Header length calculations consumed all available TBS\n4. Other resource allocation issues prevented data transmission\n\nThis missing log made it extremely difficult to debug RRC connection issues and data stall problems in the field. The added log statement provides critical debugging information including the exact values of `ta_len`, `sdu_length_total`, and `header_length_total` that resulted in the decision to skip transmission.\n\n"
}